The value of the field is the total amount of interest paid to financial institution exempt from withholding under DTA. Australia has entered into taxation agreements with more than 40 countries. Tax treaties, which are also referred to as tax conventions or double tax agreements (DTA). They prevent double taxation and fiscal evasion and foster cooperation between Australia and other international tax authorities by enforcing their respective tax laws. The company will only be affected by a tax treaty if it is a resident of Australia or the other treaty country. For more information refer to Taxation Ruling 2001/3 Income Tax: Interpreting Australia's Double Tax Agreements.
